<h3>Overview of Grant Fraud Investigations</h3>
<b>December 9, 2014</b>
<p><b>Presenters:</b> Ken Dieffenbach, Senior Special Agent, Fraud Division, Office of the Inspector General, U.S. Department of Justice</p>
<p>This webinar provides an overview of the Office of the Inspector General (OIG) and its role in detecting and deterring waste, fraud, abuse, and misconduct in DOJ-funded programs. A question and answer (Q&A) session will follow the presentation. Program and financial points-of-contact who are: a) new to managing OVW awards; and/or b) received an FY 2014 OVW award and will not be attending an in-person grantee orientation should participate.</p>
